[b]Ambieye[/b] is a comprehensive solution to control digitally connected lighting, such as the Philips Hue.


[list]
[*][url=http://bit.ly/lightpro]Lightswitch[/url] is a browser extension to control the Philip Hue lights easily from Chrome.
                                 
[*][url=http://bit.ly/shinehue]Shine[/url] is an apo for Mac, PC, Linux, Chromebooks to control Philip Hue lights. 
                                 
[*][url=http://ambieye.com/]Ambieye.com[/url] is an online portal for controlling lights from the browser.
[/list]
                                 
                                 
                                 [b]Setup[/b]

1. After installing you will need connectivity to Philips Hue MeetHue.com Portal, or you can enter an IP address of the bridge yourself.
2. When the bridge is found, you see the 'press the link button' message - press the middle button on the bridge to authenticate the extension. 
3. Control your lights from while on the same WiFi network! About Philip Hue lightsTo use this app you would have to buy and setup the [url=http://bit.ly/lightswitchhue]Philips Hue starter kit[/url]. 


The Hue lights are digitally controlled lights using WiFi and Zigbee protocols. 
                                 For updates, bugs and ideas, please contact apistarter@gmail.com, 
                                 [url=http://sadakov.com/]http://sadakov.com[/url], or on tweeter at [url=http://twitter.com/ambieye]@ambieye[/url].


I would love to hear feedback and your ideas!A free version of the [url=http://bit.ly/huelights]Lightswitch for Chrome[/url] is available. Thanks for the contribution to home automation and your time!


Made in ♥ New York City by Dmitry Sadakov.
                                 
                                 
